            <title>[HBASE-18118] Default storage policy if not configured cannot be &quot;NONE&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-18118</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HBase can&apos;t use &apos;NONE&apos; as default storage policy if not configured because HDFS supports no such policy. This policy name was probably available in a precommit or early version of the HDFS side support for heterogeneous storage. Now the best default is &apos;HOT&apos;. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
